pageProduct.name: Scholl Party Feet Gel Heel Cushions
pageProduct.description:
Information

Effective cushioning and protection for your feet

Partying with friends, shopping trips or sightseeing - your feet have to handle a lot when you are out and about. Don't let your feet spoil the fun. Scholl Party Feet Heel Cushions give your feet comfort and protection. This insert is placed under the heel to cushion and protect it against pressure.

Cushioning

Our GelActiv Technology helps provide effective cushioning and protection for your feet

Discreet design

Party Feet inserts are designed to be slim and discreet. They are also transparent, which makes them also invisible in the shoe.

Everywhere you go

Sightseeing, shopping trips, partying with friends or just walks in the park - Party Feet Inserts give you comfort wherever you go.

Firmly in place

Party Feet Inserts are designed with non-slip technology so the insert doesn't slip in the shoe.

General Information

Scholl Party Feet Heel Cushions with GelActiv technology protect against pressure and cushions the heel

Scholl Heel Cushions are ultra-thin, soft gel cushions that help cushion and protect your heel against pressure. With non-slip technology, Party Feet Heel Cushions are designed not to slip in shoes. With clear gel, slim and discreet design, the Heel Cushions fit comfortably in most womens shoes

Size: 1 Pair

Reusable?: true

KEY FEATURES

• With GelActiv Technology
• Clear gel, ultra slim and discreet
• Non-slip technology
• Fits comfortably in most womens shoes

Warnings

Discontinue use if discomfort or irritation occurs, do not use in contact with broken or irritated skin.

Directions

Place in your shoe under the heel of your foot.

- Trial placement in the shoe before removing the protective film.
- Ensure the cushion sits in the heel area with the larger rounded end at the back.
- Peel protective film off cushions and apply to the shoe sticky side down.
- Reposition if required, ensuring the cushions are in the same position in each shoe.
- Take care when removing, pull slowly and gently out of the shoe, applying pressure to the shoe insole next to the cushion with the other hand.
- Replace after 6 months or first signs of wear.

Recyclable Packaging?: Yes

Recycling Code: 1 PET(E)| 21 PAP

Washable?: true
